  "clinical_criteria": [
    "Individuals 60 days old or older",
    "Two or more in-person visits on separate calendar days with ICD-9 code 691.8 PLUS two or more prescriptions for atopic dermatitis-related medications",
    "OR three or more in-person visits on separate calendar days with ICD-9 code 691.8",
    "Controls must have two or more in-person visits in the last 5 years",
    "Controls must have no diagnosis code for atopic dermatitis (691.8)",
    "Controls must have no history of relevant medications",
    "Controls must have no exclusionary ICD-9 codes"
  ],
  "algorithm_summary": "This atopic dermatitis phenotype algorithm identifies cases through two pathways: (1) individuals \u226560 days old with 2+ visits coded with ICD-9 691.8 plus 2+ prescriptions for AD-related medications, or (2) individuals \u226560 days old with 3+ visits coded with ICD-9 691.8. Cases are excluded if they have specific skin conditions, immune disorders, or other confounding diagnoses. Controls are individuals \u226560 days old with 2+ visits in 5 years, no AD diagnosis, no AD medications, and no exclusionary conditions. The algorithm includes extensive medication lists covering topical corticosteroids, calcineurin inhibitors, antihistamines, oral corticosteroids, and other treatments, along with comprehensive exclusion criteria to ensure phenotype specificity.",
